      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://thepiedpieper.github.io/images/dna.pdf&#34;&gt;DNA&lt;/a&gt;
Watson and Crick&amp;rsquo;s hypothesis had immediately suggested a possible self-replication method for DNA because of complementarity in base pairing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At this junction, possible modes of DNA replication:
Conservative /  Semi-conservative /  Dispersive&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meselson-Stahl Experiment proves replication is semi-conservative&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bacteria grown in N(15) medium incorporate N14 in a light medium - CsCl density gradient centrifugation revealed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identification of Replication Fork&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;John Cairns identified the replication fork by allowing replicating DNA in cells to incorporate tritiated thymidine. Each daughter molecule contains a radioactive strand and a cold strand.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
